270","1290":"1290","Parr, Lancashire, England":"Parr, Lancashire, England","Parr Hall, Prescott, Lancashire, England":"Parr, Lancashire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Parr","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Parr in Lancashire, or from residence at an enclosure (Middle English <i>parr</i>, Old English <i>pearr</i>).","German: from Middle Low German <i>parre</i> ‘parish, district, minister's house’; a metonymic occupational name for a parson or for someone who worked in a parsonage or manse. Compare   Pfarr  .","English: variant of   Pear   with the common late Middle English and early modern English change of <i>-er</i>- to <i>-ar-</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Pare","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Henri, Laurent, Normand, Fernand, Alphonse, Clermont, Elphege, Alain, Benoit, Gaston, Girard.","French (<b>Paré</b>): occupational name for someone who finished cloth, from the past participle of <i>parer</i> ‘to prepare’.","English: variant of   Parr  ."]},{"name":"Parman","meanings":["Americanized form of German <b>Parmann</b>: variant of   Parr  .","Possibly an altered form of German <b>Bärmann</b> (see   Barmann  ).","English: variant of   Pearman  ."]},{"name":"Porr","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Ulrike, Gunther.","German:","metonymic occupational name for a grower or seller of leeks or other vegetables, from Middle High German <i>porre</i>, <i>pforre</i> ‘leek’ (from Latin <i>porrum</i>)."]},{"name":"Pfarr","meanings":["South German: from Middle High German <i>pfarr</i> ‘district, parish’ or <i>pfarre(r)</i> ‘parish priest’, hence an occupational name for a parson, or a topographic name for someone who lived near the parsonage."]}]},{"name":"Adam","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: The Scripture name, in Hebrew, Adham, signifying 'man;' literally earthy, red earth; Rudolph, however, says the name in Ethiopic means ' to be fair, beautiful.' Hence the nurse-name Addy, little Adam."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":25,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Adam D' Parr was born in 1265, in Parr, Lancashire, England as the son of Ooare De Parre. He married Alice Hindley. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1303, in his hometown, at the age of 38."},"et":{"1265–1303":"1265–1303","1270–1348":"1270–1348","1295–1351":"1295–1351","1250–1310":"1250–1310","1348":"1348","1303":"1303","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","1351":"1351","1295":"1295","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","Parr, Lancashire, England":"Parr, Lancashire, England","Parr Hall, Prescott, Lancashire, England":"Parr, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1265–1303":"1265–1303","1270–1348":"1270–1348","1295–1351":"1295–1351","1250–1310":"1250–1310","1348":"1348","1303":"1303","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","1351":"1351","1295":"1295","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","Parr, Lancashire, England":"Parr, Lancashire, England","Parr Hall, Prescott, Lancashire, England":"Parr, Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"1265–1303":"1265–1303","1270–1348":"1270–1348","1295–1351":"1295–1351","1250–1310":"1250–1310","1348":"1348","1303":"1303","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","1351":"1351","1295":"1295","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","Parr, Lancashire, England":"Parr, Lancashire, Angleterre","Parr Hall, Prescott, Lancashire, England":"Parr, Lancashire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Adam D' Parr est né en 1265, à Parr, Lancashire, Angleterre, fils de Ooare De Parre. Il a épousé Alice Hindley. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1303, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 38 ans."},"de":{"1265–1303":"1265–1303","1270–1348":"1270–1348","1295–1351":"1295–1351","1250–1310":"1250–1310","1348":"1348","1303":"1303","1310":"1310","1265":"12